{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"12507","heading":"Penalties","label":"12507 Penalties","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/stII/ptH/ch125","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs12507","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Historical and Revision NotesRevised section 12507This section establishes criminal and civil penalties for certain violations of chapter 125 of title 46 (as enacted by this Act).","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateSection effective , with certain exceptions and qualifications, see , set out as a note under .Jan. 1, 1989section 107 of Pub. L. 100–710section 31301 of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":null,"label":"a","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs12507%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs12507%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"provides false information to the Secretary of Transportation or a State issuing authority regarding the identification of a vessel under this chapter; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs12507%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"tampers with, removes, or falsifies the unique vessel identification number assigned to a vessel under .section 12502 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":null,"label":"b","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs12507%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs12507%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"provides false information to the Secretary or a State issuing authority regarding the identification of a vessel under this chapter;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs12507%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"violates ; orsection 12502 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs12507%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"fails to comply with requirements prescribed by the Secretary under .section 12505 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":null,"label":"c","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs12507%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A vessel involved in a violation of this chapter, or regulation under this chapter, and its equipment, may be seized by, and forfeited to, the Government.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":null,"label":"d","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/s12507","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs12507%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"If a person, not an individual, is involved in a violation of this chapter, the president or chief executive of the person also is subject to any penalty provided under this section.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
